cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a method for robotic manipulation using deep networks and synthetic data to recognize primitive shapes for object grasping. The focus is on robotics and computer vision, which suggests that the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses deep networks, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a likely category. The use of synthetic data and the proposed ranking algorithm suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely categories. Finally, the paper deals with grasping, which suggests cs.GR (Graphics) as a possible category.
